tool_description: Cryptographic API for encryption, decryption, authentication
name: Crypto Engine API
title: Crypto Engine API

api_list.name: /zk13/initialize
api_list.description: STEP 01 - it should be performed only by the Prover or only by the Verifier. Initialize the ZK13 algorithm to get viable values to produce the Proof of Authentication. Input: none Output: json, Initialization
api_list.code:
import requests

url = "https://crypto-engine-api.p.rapidapi.com/zk13/initialize"

headers = {
            "X-RapidAPI-Key": "SIGN-UP-FOR-KEY",
            "X-RapidAPI-Host": "crypto-engine-api.p.rapidapi.com"
        }

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
print(response.json())

generator.description: The generator of the Proof of Authentication and the Verification.  The correct result should be an hexadecimal string of 2 bytes, usually fixed at "02".

key.description: The common secret used to produce the Proof of Authentication and the Verification.  The correct result should be an hexadecimal string of 256 bytes that changes each time is invoked.

prime.description: Large prime number used as modulus for producing the Proof of Authentication and the Verification.  The correct result should be an hexadecimal string of 256 bytes.
